# Python-list-in-Cplusplus-2
Basically Python list data structure made in C++ 

if you create a List object 
```
List<int> arr;
or 
List<float> arr;
```

you will be able to apply these things:

```
arr.append();
arr.clear;
arr.pop();
arr.index(int index);
arr.sum();
arr.pmin();
arr.pmax();
arr.insert(int index, int value);
arr.extend(arr2);
arr.sort();
arr.count(int value);
arr.len();
arr.remove(int value);
arr.reverse();

pmax(arr);
pmin(arr);
plen(arr);
sum(arr);
```
That's all folks! 

feel free to contribute to the project if you want to.
